args:
The prince and his friends head to Paradise,
a village on the northern continent. There, they
help a group of undercover apostles investigate
rumors of a memory-manipulating woman
called Madame. The apostles suspect that a
sealing stone may lie at the root of the incident.
When I heard a band of kidnappers was\nmaking trouble on the northern continent, I\nenvisioned mightier foes. What a letdown.
You took my men out just like that?!\nWho the blazes are you?
I am the apostle Basileus. As is my office,\nI shall administer Her will.
Yes! The apostle ace does it again!
Pinon, how fares the captured child?
We've got him in protective custody, sir!
Oh jeez... I'm no good with crying.\nUm, hey, everything's okay now...
Dry your tears, young man.\nA smile better suits a brave boy like you.
You showed a lot of courage today.
I've entrusted the rescued child to the\nclosest church.

Fine work. I must say, though: you are
too quick to let tears rattle your nerves.
If you would call yourself an apostle,
you must temper your composure.
(There's nothing quite like getting told\noff by someone you greatly admire.\nReeeal smooth, Pinon.)
You are yet unwise to the world in many\nways. Even so, I sense within you the\npotential to rise higher than any other.
I expect much of you in the years to come.\nDo not let me down.
Sir! I promise I won't, sir!
Paradise\nA mountain village in North Grastaea

In the midst of journeying in North Grastaea,
the prince and his friends encounter a lost girl.
They offer to reunite her with her wayward
parents, bringing them to Paradise.
Whoever named this place wasn't lyin'.\nIt sure looks peaceful.
Your parents are here, right? You said you\nwere headed here to meet up with them,\nbut got lost along the way, if I recall.

Mm-hm. They heard there was an amazing
person who can solve any problem here,
so they came to ask them for help.
But then they didn't come back...

HEL-LOOOOO and WELCOME! Here for
some sightseeing? A place to rest your
weary bones? Or are you looking for the
next place to call home?
We're actually searching for some folks.\nThis little one's parents were supposed to\nhave come here.
Hm... That's odd. I don't recall hearing\nabout anyone with kids being here.
Some help you are, lady.\nThey totally WERE here.
Dad? Mom? Why're you still here?\nIt's time to come home.
Er... Do you know this girl?
No, I don't. She must be confusing us\nwith someone else.
You can say that all you want, but the fact\nof the matter is that I've never seen you in\nmy life.
Why are you guys being so mean to me?\nCome on, Dad... Mom...
You just don't quit. Listen!\nWe aren't your parents!
Whoa, slow down there.\nNo need to be shovin' kids around.\nYou people really don't know her?
We're newlyweds. We don't have any kids.\nWho just saunters on up to a couple and\nstarts making weird insinuations like that?
Pardon me, citizens. I'm with Paradise's\nneighborhood watch. Is something amiss?
Oh, I'm so glad you're here. These\nstrange people won't leave us alone.
I see, I see. Let me have a word with\nthese people and—Oh no!
Pinon! What are you doing here?
Yeah. We worked together to investigate\nand resolve the wroth incident down south.
BAAAAAD PEOPLE! Stop lying and\ntrying to disturb the peace in town!\nTime for you to SKEDADDLE!
(I can't let it get out that I'm an apostle.\nLeave town and wait for me in the nearby\nwoods. I'll come and explain.)
I had some other colleagues bring the girl\nback to her house. She did look quite hurt,\nthough...
You think they really weren't her parents?\nOr could there be something else going\non here?
Sorry to make you all wait for me.
Oh, hi, Pinon. Who are your friends?\nI saw them with you earlier, but didn't\nrecognize them.
I'll introduce you. These are my superiors,\nRyszarda and Faris.
Um, it's nice to meet you.\nPinon has told me much about you.
I saw what went down in town.\nYou get a passing grade from me\nfor being quick on the uptake.
And I am Little Pi's dear mama, Gabriel!\nThank you for always keeping my little\ngirl out of trouble!
Ahem! Gabriel is the angel I share a Sigil\nwith, so she's like a foster mother to me.
Apostles and angels associated with the\nnorthern church... What duty brings you to\nParadise?
A kind of spiritual community has cropped\nup around a person there called Madame.
She seems to possess a curious power,\nand she uses it to aid people in distress.
Word is that Madame can rewrite people's\nmemories—make bad ones go away,\nor even plant the seed of happy ones.
Did you say ＂rewrite memories＂? That\ncould explain why those people said they\ndidn't recognize their daughter!
As I hear it, a host of people have flocked\nto Madame, discarding their memories\nand pasts in the process.
But if they're forkin' over their brain juice\nwillingly, that doesn't explain why you all\nfelt the need to get involved.
Are you familiar with the matter of the\nsealing stones?

You mean the forbidden stones that seal
away demons? The miasma that flooded
out of the one we saw drove people to
barbarity and revived an evil menace.
Several sealing stones exist, and the\nelements necessary for unsealing each\none differ.

According to Church documents, there is
a sealing stone that robs the afflicted of
their memories and—you guessed it—
revives the demon inside it.
You can't mean to say that Madame's\npowers spring from such a fell source?!
We don't know for sure. That's why the\nChurch ordered us to go undercover in\nParadise and investigate the situation.
I see. How about we lend you a hand,\nthen?
You're outsiders. There's no logical reason\nfor you to be a part of our investigation.

Now hold on just a minute. These people
are no strangers to demons. In the event
that Madame's power DOES come from
a sealing stone—
It...would behoove us to have as many\npeople on the problem as possible, right?\nFor maximum peace of mind.
We're well aware of the threat demons\npose. If Madame seeks to revive one of\nthem, we can't just turn a blind eye.
Furthermore, even if that child's parents\nwanted their memories to be rewritten, if\nthey're pawns in a plot to rouse a demon...
I wouldn't be able to sleep at night\nlettin' somethin' that dastardly slide.
I...suppose it's better to have you close at\nhand than let you run about on your own.
But we're only adding one of you to our\ninvestigation. It'll arouse suspicion if we\nsniff around in such a large group.
Allow me, then. I'm the one who\nfirst brought it up, after all.
You'll stand out in that outfit, though, so\nit would be better if you changed clothes.
Actually, I've got a little homework\nfor the rest of you in the meantime.
Yes.\nThey'll be making a cleansing fount.
